http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/MSF-flays-expulsion-of-UoH-scholars/article13995454.ece

Madiga Student Federation, Acharya Nagarjuna University, Guntur, has denounced the expulsion of five Dalit research scholars from the hostels of University of Hyderabad. In a statement, MSF president P. Abhishek termed the action of Executive Council of the University as ‘anti Dalit’ and discriminatory in nature. He said that though the fact finding committee has not found conclusive evidence of any violence on the campus, the EC chaired by Vice-Chancellor P. Appa Rao took the decision of expelling the five scholars.